# Accessibility Rules (无障碍)

Every interactive element MUST be VoiceOver-accessible. Every animation MUST respect ReduceMotion.

## VoiceOver Labels

```swift
// ✅ GOOD - unique, localized label describing the item
.accessibilityLabel(Text("a11y.screenshot.label \(screenshot.createdAt.formatted(...))"))

// ❌ BAD - same generic label for every item in a list
.accessibilityLabel(Text("detail.title"))  // all cards read the same

// ❌ BAD - hardcoded English
.accessibilityLabel("Start capture")
```

## Hints & Traits

```swift
// ✅ GOOD - hint explains what happens on activation
.accessibilityHint(Text("a11y.capture.hint"))
.accessibilityAddTraits(.isButton)

// ✅ GOOD - selected state for toggleable items
.accessibilityAddTraits(isSelected ? [.isButton, .isSelected] : .isButton)
```

## Decorative vs Informative Images

```swift
// ✅ GOOD - decorative icon hidden from VoiceOver
Image(systemName: "sparkles")
    .accessibilityHidden(true)

// ✅ GOOD - informative image with description
Image(decorative: screenshot.image, scale: 1.0)  // already hidden
```

## Container Grouping

```swift
// ✅ GOOD - card reads as single element
.accessibilityElement(children: .combine)

// Use for: cards, list rows, instruction steps, info displays
```

## Reduce Motion

```swift
// ✅ GOOD - the shouldReduceMotion pattern (also respects elder mode)
@Environment(\.accessibilityReduceMotion) private var reduceMotion
@Environment(\.userMode) private var userMode
private var shouldReduceMotion: Bool { reduceMotion || userMode == .elder }

// ✅ GOOD - guard all animations
.animation(shouldReduceMotion ? nil : SCTheme.Animation.standard, value: x)
.transition(shouldReduceMotion ? .identity : .opacity)

// ✅ GOOD - skip animated backgrounds entirely
if shouldReduceMotion {
    // static gradient fallback
} else if #available(iOS 18.0, macOS 15.0, *) {
    AnimatedMeshBackground()
}

// ✅ GOOD - guard onAppear animations
.onAppear {
    guard !shouldReduceMotion else { return }
    withAnimation(...) { pulseScale = 1.15 }
}

// ❌ BAD - unguarded symbolEffect
base.symbolEffect(.bounce, options: .repeating)  // ignores preference
```

## Checklist for every new view

- [ ] Every `Button` / interactive element has `.accessibilityLabel` (localized)
- [ ] Non-obvious actions have `.accessibilityHint`
- [ ] Appropriate `.accessibilityAddTraits` (`.isButton`, `.isHeader`, `.isSelected`)
- [ ] Decorative images use `.accessibilityHidden(true)` or `Image(decorative:)`
- [ ] Cards / grouped content use `.accessibilityElement(children: .combine)`
- [ ] List items have UNIQUE labels (include date/name/index)
- [ ] All `withAnimation`, `.animation()`, `.transition()`, `.symbolEffect()` guarded
- [ ] `shouldReduceMotion` pattern used (combines system pref + elder mode)
